evidence: The effects of Al on microstructures, and mechnical properties of AlxMoNbTaTiV are investigated, which verified the results of calculated dendritic microstructure and BCC structure.

The as-cast alloys are composed of a major BCC#1 structure and a very small number of BCC#2 structure, which can be regarded as dendritic and inter-dendritic structures. The density also decreases from 9.33 � 0.01g/cm 3 , to 8.15 � 0.01g/cm 3 . At the same time, the hardness increases gradually from 421.6 � 7.9Hv to 574.8 � 9.6 Hv. At room temperature, the yield strength increases monotonously from 1228 MPa to 1391 MPa with the increase of aluminum content.

Conclusion AlxMoNbTaTiV alloys were synthesized combining typical highentropy alloy and CALPHAD methods. The Al element are introduced into the single-phase BCC solid solution as solute. The results are summarized as follows: 1. All alloys exhibited typical dendritic structure as predicted by the CALPHAD method. The elements with high melting temperature often occupy the center of dendrites, and the elements with low melting temperature segregate in inter-dendrites. 2. As the Al content increases, the lattice constant decreased from 3.211 Å to 3.199 Å. The yield strength increases from 1228 MPa to 1391 MPa, the hardness increases from 421 Hv to 575 Hv.
